WEBVTT

00:00.987 --> 00:02.879
Eight years ago, I was lead prosecutor

00:02.913 --> 00:04.833
on a murder trial
that divided the country.

00:06.107 --> 00:08.442
When the jury found
movie star Sevvy Johnson

00:08.476 --> 00:10.611
not guilty of double homicid,

00:10.645 --> 00:11.812
I was devastated.

00:11.846 --> 00:13.547
You did everything you could, Maya.

00:13.581 --> 00:16.216
I left that life
and everyone in it behind.

00:16.251 --> 00:17.951
But then the unthinkable happened.

00:17.986 --> 00:18.785
He killed again.

00:18.820 --> 00:20.087
You have to come back, Maya.

00:20.121 --> 00:22.289
This time, we're gonna get him.

00:22.323 --> 00:23.624
I found this on the porch.

00:23.658 --> 00:25.492
There's no card. Secret admirer?

00:25.526 --> 00:27.261
Your stalker? He's back?

00:27.295 --> 00:28.495
A detective came by my place.

00:28.529 --> 00:30.297
They always want to talk to the ex.

00:30.331 --> 00:32.833
Maya Travis has you and Jessica on tape

00:32.867 --> 00:34.601
the night before she was murdered.

00:34.636 --> 00:36.637
There's a mole in this office.

00:36.671 --> 00:38.472
No one leaves this office
until we find out who it is.

00:38.506 --> 00:41.061
And everybody takes a lie-detector test.

00:41.709 --> 00:43.443
I know it's you.

00:43.478 --> 00:44.874
- We found the mole.
- Who?

00:44.908 --> 00:46.081
It was a janitor on the night shift.

00:46.116 --> 00:47.347
He's been fired.

00:47.382 --> 00:48.982
What was Sevvy's DNA doing on it?

00:49.017 --> 00:51.084
This is it. Sevvy was there.

00:51.119 --> 00:53.854
Matthew. We've got him!

00:53.888 --> 00:55.756
On a little getaway?

00:55.790 --> 00:57.658
Something like that.

01:02.330 --> 01:04.998
Sevvy Johnson. LAPD. We have
a warrant for your arrest.

01:05.033 --> 01:06.133
Open up. Mm-hmm.

01:06.167 --> 01:08.535
Did you check the guest quarters?

01:08.569 --> 01:10.671
- He's not at the Malibu house.
- Yes. Thank you.

01:10.705 --> 01:12.506
He's not at the desert estate either.

01:12.540 --> 01:14.441
Housekeeper
hasn't seen Sevvy since yesterday.

01:14.475 --> 01:16.610
Okay, so, he's not at
any of his residences.

01:16.644 --> 01:18.779
Let's check out his favorite
restaurants, hotels.

01:18.813 --> 01:21.368
He's got to be somewhere.
50 bucks says he ran.

01:21.402 --> 01:22.683
Let's not even go there.

01:22.717 --> 01:24.672
Just got a hit on Sevvy's car.

01:25.019 --> 01:26.716
He's at the Van Nuys Airport.

01:27.592 --> 01:29.122
Uh-huh.

01:29.157 --> 01:30.657
I'm gonna call Wolf.

01:30.692 --> 01:32.359
Ow, ah.

01:32.393 --> 01:34.494
Gentle, gentle, gentle. Oh.

01:39.934 --> 01:42.536
Maya. To what do I owe this pleasure?

01:42.570 --> 01:45.005
I have a warrant for
your client's arrest.

01:46.674 --> 01:48.542
- I see.
- But it appears he's fled.

01:48.576 --> 01:50.310
His car is at the Van Nuys Airport.

01:50.345 --> 01:53.213
Whoa. Whoa, whoa, innocent men don't run.

01:53.247 --> 01:55.849
I'm sure there's a perfectly
boring explanation for this.

01:55.883 --> 01:56.983
You know the drill, Wolf.

01:57.018 --> 01:59.686
Produce your client.
Yeah, now that you mention it,

01:59.721 --> 02:02.689
he did say he was planning
a sojourn up to Napa.

02:02.724 --> 02:04.591
Something about a-a wine tasting.

02:04.625 --> 02:07.627
Wherever he is, he's not on the run.

02:08.642 --> 02:10.910
The son of a bitch is on the run.

02:10.935 --> 02:12.402
More champagne?

02:14.969 --> 02:16.570
Thanks, Marie.

02:19.107 --> 02:20.674
Thank you.

